replies.bodyText:
ess.getPermissionsHandler().setUseSuperperms(ess.getSettings().useBukkitPermissions());
ess.getPermissionsHandler().checkPermissions();
ess.getPermissionsHandler().registerContext(...);
can all be moved to onEnable, you're softdepending on LuckPerms now anyway.
Then just keep a single call to
ess.getPermissionsHandler().checkPermissions();
in the plugin enable listener to catch other permission plugins.
The call to
ess.getPermissionsHandler().unregisterContexts();
definitely needs to be moved to onDisable. In it's current position, contexts are going to be unregistered every time any plugin is disabled.
